{"title_page": "Border Guards Corps (Egypt)", "text_new": "{{Userspace draft|source=ArticleWizard|date=April 2020}} \n{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name                     = Egyptian Border Guard\n| dates                         = 1878 - ''Present''\n| country                       = {{flag|Egypt}}\n| branch                        = [[Egyptian Army]]\n| type                          = \n| role                          = Border Guard\n| size                          = 12,000 - 25,000\n| garrison                      = \n| motto                         = \n| colors                        = \n| mascot                        = \n| current_commander             = Major-General Arkan Harb, Ayman Shehata\n| native_name                   = \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f\n}}\n'''The Egyptian Border Guard''' are a corps of the [[Egyptian Army]] tasked with the protection of Egypt's land and sea borders. The corps is in charge of protecting the Suez Canal and stopping the movement of illegal immigration, smuggling, human trafficking, and illegal narcotics into and out of Egypt.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150608084840/http://akhbarelyom.com/news/newdetails/217825/1/-%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AD%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84.html|title=\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0647\u0631\u0629 \u0644\u062a\u0623\u0645\u064a\u0646 \u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f \u0645\u0635\u0631|date=2015-06-08|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> \n\nIn total, the Guard is responsible for over 6000 km of land and sea border to secure. They work in cooperation with the other branches of the Egyptian Military to intercept infiltration. The guard has a particular responsibility in securing the 13 km Gaza Strip border where thousands of tunnels have brought in narcotics, weapons, and terrorists into the Sinai.\n\n== History ==\nOriginally founded as the Frontier Corps in 1878, in 1917, under the administration of [[Hussein Kamel of Egypt|Sultan Hussein Kamel]], the Department of Border and Coastal Management was created a sub-department of the [[Ministry of Finance (Egypt)|Ministry of Finance]], and under it the Border Guard was founded. In 1939, the Coast Guard was separated into the Ministry of War, later forming the basis for the founding of the Egyptian Navy. On 6 July, 1972, the Command of the Border Guard was created from the merging of the other departments and was given to the Army, rejoining the Coast Guard and Border Guard.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\nThe Egyptian Border Guard participated in [[World War II]] including stopping the sabotage of [[Matrouh Governorate|Matrouh]]-[[Alexandria]] railway in the [[Fouka, Egypt|Fukah]] region by German soldiers.\n\nIn the Six Day War, the Egyptian Border Guard intercepted and captured Israeli Frogman in the Port of Alexandria. On 21 October, 196, Egyptian Coast Guard sunk the [[HMS Zealous (R39)|INS Eilat.]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918123647/https://www.vetogate.com/2538919|title=\u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u0641\u064a\u062a\u0648: \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f.. \u062d\u0635\u0646 \u064a\u062d\u0645\u064a \u0645\u0635\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0637\u0648\u0644 6 \u0622\u0644\u0627\u0641 \u0643\u064a\u0644\u0648|date=2018-09-18|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n== Notable Former Members ==\nVeto Gate lists the following as former members of the Guard:<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n* President [[Mohamed Naguib]]\n** Commander of the Border Brigade from 1942-1943\n** Director of the Royal Border Force from 1950-1952\n* President [[Anwar Sadat|Mohamed Anwar El-Sadat]]\n** Officer in the Wireless Border Battalion from 1941-1942\n* Minister of Information [[Mohamed Abdel-Qader Hatem]]\n** Served at the border administration from 1940-1945\n* Minister of Defense [[Mohamed Abdel Ghani el-Gamasy|Mohamed Abdel-Ghani El-Gamasy]]\n** Intelligence officer for the border administration from 1941-1945\n** Assistant Director for Intelligence at the border administration from 1952-1954\n\n== Structure ==\n'''H.Q. Command & 5 Field H.Q.'''\n\n* 20 Battalions: 12,000 men, mostly [[Bedouins]], lightly armed paramilitary forces equipped with remote sensors, night-vision binoculars, communications vehicles, and high-speed motorboats and responsible for:\n** Border surveillance: 10 battalions\n** General peacekeeping: 2 battalions\n** Drug interdiction: 5 battalions\n** Prevention of smuggling: 3 battalions\n\n== References ==<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Egyptian Army}}\n[[Category:Military units and formations of Egypt]]\n[[Category:Border guards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Userspace draft|source=ArticleWizard|date=April 2020}} \n{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name                     = Egyptian Border Guard\n| dates                         = 1878 - ''Present''\n| country                       = {{flag|Egypt}}\n| branch                        = [[Egyptian Army]]\n| type                          = \n| role                          = Border Guard\n| size                          = 12,000 - 25,000\n| garrison                      = \n| motto                         = \n| colors                        = \n| mascot                        = \n| current_commander             = Major-General Arkan Harb, Ayman Shehata\n| native_name                   = \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f\n}}\n'''The Egyptian Border Guard''' are a corps of the [[Egyptian Army]] tasked with the protection of Egypt's land and sea borders. The corps is in charge of protecting the Suez Canal and stopping the movement of illegal immigration, smuggling, human trafficking, and illegal narcotics into and out of Egypt.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150608084840/http://akhbarelyom.com/news/newdetails/217825/1/-%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AD%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84.html|title=\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0647\u0631\u0629 \u0644\u062a\u0623\u0645\u064a\u0646 \u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f \u0645\u0635\u0631|date=2015-06-08|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref> \n\nIn total, the Guard is responsible for over 6000km of land and sea border to secure. They work in cooperation with the other branches of the Egyptian Military to intercept infiltration. The guard has a particular responsibility in securing the 13 km Gaza Strip border where thousands of tunnels have brought in narcotics, weapons, and terrorists into the Sinai.\n\n== History ==\nOriginally founded as the Frontier Corps in 1878, in 1917, under the administration of [[Hussein Kamel of Egypt|Sultan Hussein Kamel]], the Department of Border and Coastal Management was created a sub-department of the [[Ministry of Finance (Egypt)|Ministry of Finance]], and under it the Border Guard was founded. In 1939, the Coast Guard was separated into the Ministry of War, later forming the basis for the founding of the Egyptian Navy. On 6 July, 1972, the Command of the Border Guard was created from the merging of the other departments and was given to the Army, rejoining the Coast Guard and Border Guard.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\nThe Egyptian Border Guard participated in [[World War II]] including stopping the sabotage of [[Matrouh Governorate|Matrouh]]-[[Alexandria]] railway in the [[Fouka, Egypt|Fukah]] region by German soldiers.\n\nIn the Six Day War, the Egyptian Border Guard intercepted and captured Israeli Frogman in the Port of Alexandria. On 21 October, 196, Egyptian Coast Guard sunk the [[HMS Zealous (R39)|INS Eilat.]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918123647/https://www.vetogate.com/2538919|title=\u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u0641\u064a\u062a\u0648: \u062d\u0631\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f.. \u062d\u0635\u0646 \u064a\u062d\u0645\u064a \u0645\u0635\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0637\u0648\u0644 6 \u0622\u0644\u0627\u0641 \u0643\u064a\u0644\u0648|date=2018-09-18|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n== Notable Former Members ==\nVeto Gate listens the following as former members of the Guard<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n* President [[Mohamed Naguib]]\n** Commander of the Border Brigade from 1942-1943\n** Director of the Royal Border Force from 1950-1952\n* President [[Anwar Sadat|Mohamed Anwar El-Sadat]]\n** Officer in the Wireless Border Battalion from 1941-1942\n* Minister of Information [[Mohamed Abdel-Qader Hatem]]\n** Served at the border administration from 1940-1945\n* Minister of Defense [[Mohamed Abdel Ghani el-Gamasy|Mohamed Abdel-Ghani El-Gamasy]]\n** Intelligence officer for the border administration from 1941-1945\n** Assistant Director for Intelligence at the border administration from 1952-1954\n\n== Structure ==\n'''H.Q. Command & 5 Field H.Q.'''\n\n* 20 Battalions: 12,000 men, mostly [[Bedouins]], lightly armed paramilitary forces equipped with remote sensors, night-vision binoculars, communications vehicles, and high-speed motorboats and responsible for:\n** Border surveillance: 10 battalions\n** General peacekeeping: 2 battalions\n** Drug interdiction: 5 battalions\n** Prevention of smuggling: 3 battalions\n\n== References ==<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Egyptian Army}}\n[[Category:Military units and formations of Egypt]]\n[[Category:Border guards]]\n", "name_user": "AttackHelicopter51", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "