al Visuals|publisher=AerialVisuals.ca|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 61-2724 \u2013 The [[Pima Air & Space Museum]] adjacent to [[Davis\u2013Monthan Air Force Base]] in [[Tucson, Arizona]] lists an OV-1C Mohawk as a static display<ref>{{cite web|title=MOHAWK|url=http://www.pimaair.org/aircraft-by-name/item/grumman-ov-1c-mohawk|website=Pima Air & Space Museum|publisher=PimaAir.org|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 62-5856 \u2013 The Wings of Eagles Discovery Center owns an OV-1C on static display among its collection<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wingsofeagles.com/collection.cfm |title=Aircraft |publisher=Wings of Eagles Discovery Center |accessdate=2011-09-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907064230/http://www.wingsofeagles.com/collection.cfm |archivedate=2011-09-07 }}</ref>\n* 62-5860 \u2013 OV-1B on display at the United States Army Aviation Museum at [[Fort Rucker]], Alabama.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fixed Wing|url=http://www.armyaviationmuseum.org/index.php/museum/aircraft-collection/2-uncategorised/64-fixed-wing|website=United States Army Aviation Museum|publisher=Army Aviation Museum Foundation, Inc.|accessdate=6 January 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222183634/http://armyaviationmuseum.org/index.php/museum/aircraft-collection/2-uncategorised/64-fixed-wing|archivedate=22 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Airframe Dossier \u2013 Grumman OV-1B Mohawk, s/n 62-5860 US, c/n 19B|url=http://aerialvisuals.ca/AirframeDossier.php?Serial=68|website=Aerial Visuals|publisher=AerialVisuals.ca|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 62-5875 \u2013 Headquarters, [[48th Infantry Brigade Combat Team (United States)|48th Infantry Brigade Combat Team]], (Georgia Army National Guard) in [[Macon, Georgia]] displays a static OV-1D as part of an outdoor exhibit<ref name=\"Where Are They Now? MohawkStatus\"/>\n* 62-5880 \u2013 Texas Air Museum in [[Slaton, Texas]] has a modified OV-1D that was used by [[NASA]] that is on loan from the Museum of Naval Aviation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Grumman OV-1 Mohawk|url=http://www.thetexasairmuseum.org/aircraft/staticaircraft/OV-1|website=Texas Air Museum|publisher=The Texas Air Museum|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 62-5906 \u2013 Cockpit only on display at the Valiant Air Command Warbird Museum.<ref>{{cite web|title=Airframe Dossier \u2013 Grumman OV-1 Mohawk, s/n 62-5906 US Army|url=http://aerialvisuals.ca/AirframeDossier.php?Serial=66108|website=Aerial Visuals|publisher=AerialVisuals.ca|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 63-13128 - Military Aviation Preservation Society (MAPS) Air Museum (under restoration for museum display)<ref>[https://mapsairmuseum.org/ongoingaircraftrenovationprojects/ Ongoing Aircraft Renovation Projects], MAPS Air Museum, last accessed 16 November 2018</ref>\n* 64-14247 \u2013 The United States Army's [[Tobyhanna Army Depot]] in Tobyhanna, Pennsylvania, has an OV-1B on display outside the main gate access control point.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n* 64-14252 \u2013 The [[Mississippi Armed Forces Museum]] at [[Camp Shelby]] has an OV-1 on static display<ref name=\"Where Are They Now? MohawkStatus\"/>\n* 67-15959 \u2013 The [[G-Star School of the Arts]] in [[Palm Springs, Florida|West Palm Beach, Florida]] displays a static OV-1D<ref>{{cite web |title=FAA Registry - Aircraft - N-Number Inquiry |url=http://registry.faa.gov/aircraftinquiry/NNum_Results.aspx?NNumbertxt=226TT |website=registry.faa.gov |accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=G-Star Warplane on Cover of Smithsonian Magazine & in PB Post! {{!}} G-Star School of the Arts {{!}} Palm Beach County Charter High Schools |url=http://www.gstarschool.org/2017/08/20/g-star-warplane-on-cover-of-smithsonian-magazine-in-pb-post/ |website=G-Star School of the Arts {{!}} Palm Beach County Charter High Schools |accessdate=22 June 2018|date=2017-08-20 }}</ref>\n* 67-18902 \u2013 The [[Evergreen Aviation & Space Museum]] in [[McMinnvill