planeGallery/images/OV-Mohawk.jpg Mohawk at the Valiant Air Command Warbird Museum] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128170604/http://www.vacwarbirds.org/AirplaneGallery/images/OV-Mohawk.jpg |date=2012-01-28 }} retrieved 2013-06-02</ref>\n* 69-17007 \u2013 The 1st Cavalry Division Museum at Fort Hood, Texas displays a static OV-1D as part of an outdoor exhibit<ref name=\"Where Are They Now? MohawkStatus\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Gate Guards and Base Displays (not museums)|url=http://www.fencecheck.com/forums/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=1648&start=200#p253177|website=Fence Check|publisher=Liza Eckardt|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref>\n* 69-17010? \u2013 The [[United States Army Aviation Museum]] at [[Fort Rucker]], Alabama displays a static OV-1D as part of the outdoor exhibit at the intersection of Red Cloud Avenue and Ruf Avenue{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n* 69-17022 - United States Army Garrison Humphreys, Republic of Korea, OV-1 Mohawk displayed outdoors at the intersection round-a-bout of Key Street & CPX Road\n* The [[United States Army Intelligence and Security Command]] Headquarters Building at [[Fort Belvoir]], Virginia displays a static OV-1D<ref name=\"Where Are They Now? MohawkStatus\">[http://www.lotsaspace.info/OV-1Mohawk/MohawkStatus.htm Where Are They Now? MohawkStatus] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025308/http://www.lotsaspace.info/OV-1Mohawk/MohawkStatus.htm |date=2016-03-04 }} retrieved 2015-06-05</ref>\n* AZO Plane Partners in current possession of the Air Zoo's OV-1D {{Citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n* OV-1D ex-Argentine Army Aviation, in the ''Aviaci\u00f3n del Ej\u00e9rcito Argentino'' Park Buenos Aires, Argentina{{citation needed|date=March 2016}}\n\n==Specifications (OV-1D)==\n[[File:Profile OV-1 Mohawk.jpg|right|300px]]\n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=Jane's Civil and Military Aircraft Upgrades 1994\u201395<ref name=\"Janes Up94 p366-7\">Michell 1994, pp. 366\u2013367.</ref>\n|prime units?=imp\n<!--\n 